                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d888">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/2345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-02T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 2, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>538. Your 1163, October 28, 6 p.m. Your suggestion that any discussion at
                    Shanghai of court matters should be deferred until after the outcome of the
                    reported negotiations at Chungking is approved. The Department assumes that the
                    Embassy at Chungking and the Consulate General at Shanghai will continue to keep
                    the Department fully and promptly informed of developments.</p>
                <p>Sent to Shanghai. Repeated to Chungking and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
